=== Logo Replacer ===
Contributors: @bis5
Requires at least: 3.8
Tested up to: 3.8.1
License: GPLv3 or later
License URI: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html

Replace WordPress' logo to user-uploaded one at login and navigation bar.

== Description ==

(writting now)


== Installation ==

1. Create directory `/wp-content/plugins/logo-replacer` and `/wp-content/plugins/logo-replacer/inc`
1. Upload `logo-replacer.php` to the `/wp-content/plugins/logo-replacer directory
1. Upload your custom logo to the `/wp-content/plugins/logo-replacer/inc` directory. For login screen, file name is `logo.png` and 64x64 pixels recommended. (3.7.x >= ONLY)For admin header, file name is `admin.png` and 32x32 pixels recommended.
1. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress


